text: Julianne Alexandra Hough (born July 20 1988) is an American dancer, country music singer, songwriter and actress. She is best known for being a two-time champion on the ABC series Dancing with the Stars. Her first album was released May 20, 2008. She acted in the 2011 remake of the movie Footloose. Hough is the second of five children. She has three sisters and a brother.
